Package integrals

Class Function

java.lang.Object
integrals.Function
public class Function extends Object
Java class that models a function of x. The following functions are supported: sin, cos, tan, csc, sec, cot, arcsin, arccos, arctan, ln, log, sinh, cosh, tanh, sqrt. Arguments are assumed to be in radians.

    • evaluateAt

      public double evaluateAt(String value)
      Evaluates the function at a specified value and returns the result.

      This method can be used to evaluate a function at a value that is itself an expression that does not contain variables such as pi, 3*pi/2, e/2.

      Parameters:
      value - a String to evaluate the function at
      Returns:
      the value of the function at the specified number as a double
      Throws:
      ArithmeticException - if value if not in the domain

    • evaluateAt

      public double evaluateAt(String value, boolean verbose)
      Evaluates the function at a specified value and returns the result.

      This method can be used to evaluate a function at a value that is itself an expression that does not contain variables such as pi, 3*pi/2, e/2.

      Parameters:
      value - a String to evaluate the function at
      verbose - a boolean specifying whether to print out the steps involved in the evaluation. To show steps, use true.
      Returns:
      the value of the function at the specified number as a double
      Throws:
      ArithmeticException - if value if not in the domain

    • evaluate

      public static double evaluate(String expression)
      A static method that evaluates a String expression and returns a double result. This method can be used to get the double equivalent of expressions like pi, 3*pi/2, and e/2.
      Parameters:
      expression - a String expression
      Returns:
      the double value of the expression
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if expression contains variables or expression is not more than one character in length
